  16,1,"The command of God is at hand, so do not hasten it. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate ˹with Him in worship˺"
  16,2,"He sends down the angels with revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants, ˹stating:˺ “Warn ˹humanity˺ that there is no god ˹worthy of worship˺ except Me, so be mindful of Me ˹alone˺.”"
  16,3,He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. Exalted is He above what they associate with Him ˹in worship˺
  16,4,"He created humans from a sperm-drop, then—behold!—they openly challenge ˹Him˺"
  16,5,"And He created the cattle for you as a source of warmth, food, and ˹many other˺ benefits"
